<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 3:38AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Craig
and central Ottawa Counties through 430 AM CDT...
At 338 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
northwest of Vinita, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Miami...                          Vinita...
Commerce...                       Fairland...
Afton...                          Quapaw...
Bluejacket...                     Wyandotte...
Narcissa...                       Ottawa...
Picher...                         Pyramid Corners...
Twin Bridges State Park...
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 281 and 314.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
